description:
Phumzile Mlambo-Ngcuka is Former Executive Director of UN Women & Deputy President of SA Founder of Umlambo Foundation Gender Activist and Campaigner for Universal Access to Education. She was sworn into office on 19 August 2013 and brings a wealth of experience and expertise to this position, having devoted her career to issues of human rights, equality and social justice. Ms. Mlambo-Ngcuka has worked in government, private sector and civil society and was actively involved in the struggle to end apartheid in her home country of South Africa. 

From 2005 to 2008, she served as Deputy President of South Africa, overseeing programmes to combat poverty and bring the advantages of a growing economy to the poor, with a particular focus on women. Prior to this, she served as Minister of Minerals and Energy from 1999 to 2005 and Deputy Minister in the Department of Trade and Industry from 1996 to 1999. She was a Member of Parliament from 1994 to 1996 as part of South Africa’s first democratic government.

Ms. Mlambo-Ngcuka began her career as a teacher and gained international experience as a coordinator at the World YWCA in Geneva, where she established a global programme for young women. She is the founder of the Umlambo Foundation, which supports leadership and education. A longtime champion of women’s rights, she is affiliated with several organizations devoted to education, women’s empowerment and gender equality.

She has completed her PhD on education and technology at the University of Warwick, United Kingdom.
headline: Former Executive Director of UN Women & Deputy President of SA Founder of Umlambo Foundation Gender Activist and Campaigner for Universal Access to Education

description:
I am the Global Chairman and CEO for EY, one of the largest professional services organizations in the world, which in the last fiscal year achieved US$45 billion in revenues and today has approximately 400,000 people serving clients in more than 150 countries worldwide.

Prior to being elected to my current post, I served as EY Global Managing Partner – Client Service, leading the execution of the organization's global strategy and its four geographical areas and four service lines.

In 2019, I led the development of EY’s global strategy, NextWave, which expands on the purpose of 'Building a better working world' and has a clear ambition to create long-term value for all stakeholders. To execute the NextWave strategy, in 2021 EY announced investments of US$10b in EY people and technology.  
  
I helped to create the Global Innovation team to redefine how EY uses technology to both transform existing services and create new solutions. Prior to that, I held several global operating and leadership positions at EY, using my extensive experience in financial services. My global experience has equipped me with a keen understanding of cultures and clients around the world, and I am a strong advocate for the power of EY’s global organization.  

Since joining EY in 1985, I served as an Advisory and Assurance partner for many of our largest financial services accounts. Over the course of my career, I held several leadership positions at EY, including Chair of the Global Financial Services Markets Executive and Regional Managing Partner for the Americas Financial Services Organization (FSO), where I started EY Risk Management and Regulatory Services.

I’m originally from Italy and emigrated with my family to the United States when I was three years old. I was the first in my family to graduate from college, earning a BA in Chemistry from Colgate University, and an MBA from New York University’s Stern School of Business. 

I also serve on the boards of the Foundation for Empowering Citizens with Autism and Family Promise. I’m also a member of the Board of Trustees of Colgate University and the Wake Forest University Business School Board of Visitors.

On the link below you can discover more about my career and current roles.

description:
Hey what's up guys, it's Sypher! I’m a professional gamer, streamer, YouTuber, and online personality based out of Austin, Texas. With more than 20M+ followers across all platforms, we’ve been able to create an incredible community. If you are a fan – thank you from the bottom of my heart for all your support over the years. I’m consistently speechless with how incredible the ride has been.

For more than a decade, I’ve been perfecting my craft, growing my audience, and winning. There have been a lot of long nights and a lot of struggles along the way. And I know there are others out there too that are in the same boat. There are so many great content creators out there, I want to do my part in shining the light on some of the best. 

In 2020, we launched Oni Studios to give back and serve as an extension of my previous education commentary streams. Some of my most popular videos have been around my educational gameplay on Fortnite, where I tried to focus on teaching strategies, tips and tricks, and general coaching & mentorship. At their core, I was always trying to help people speed run through the years of trial and error that I went through learning Fortnite, and to gain the confidence they need to keep going whether in streaming or in life. 

Oni Studio is the next evolution of the stream and is built on a mission to give back and empower the next generation of content creators. In the past, we’ve helped bring unknown gamers to the forefront and help them to build their brands from the ground up. With Oni Studio’s upcoming 30,000 sq ft HQ, we’ll be continuing that at a scale not thought possible.  We’ll be hosting a variety of events, activations, productions, and much more!

I have worked with some awesome brands in the past like PacSun, Ralph Lauren, State Farm, and Lenovo  to spark engagement, get in front of a rapidly growing audience, and deliver some unforgettable content.
My team and I are always interested in working with and growing with potential collaborators or partners. Whether you want to collaborate directly with me or Oni Studios, please reach out via my business email SypherPK@thekinetic.co

description:
Kal Penn is an actor, writer, producer, and former Associate Director of the White House Office of Public Engagement. He is known for his starring roles in Designated Survivor, House, Mira Nair’s The Namesake, the Harold & Kumar franchise, and the patriotic immigration sit-com Sunnyside which he co-created for NBC. 

From 2009 to 2011, Kal took a sabbatical from acting to serve in the Obama/Biden administration, where he served as the President’s Liaison to Young Americans, Asian Americans and Pacific Islanders, and the Arts community. In these roles, he worked on a range of issues, including the repeal of Don’t Ask, Don’t Tell, the Affordable Care Act, Pell Grants, arts and culture programs, the DREAM Act, and rapid response to the BP Oil Spill and earthquake in Haiti.

He was a national co-chair for the Obama/Biden re-election campaign in 2012 and served on the President’s Committee for the Arts and Humanities, focusing on arts education and cultural diplomacy. Penn has taught courses at the University of Pennsylvania and the University of California, Los Angeles. Originally from New Jersey, he received his undergraduate degree in sociology, theater, film, and television at the University of California, Los Angeles, and received a graduate certificate in international security from Stanford University. 

Penn recently wrapped production on the CBS Drama, Clarice (based on Silence of the Lambs), and Freeform’s late night youth election format show Kal Penn Approves This Message. description:
In 2002 Serge Kampf, founder of Capgemini and the Board of Directors, handed me the reins of the Group and for 18 years I was CEO of this remarkable organization. In 2012 my responsibilities grew as I also became Chairman. On May 20, 2020, following our Annual General Meeting of Shareholders, Aiman Ezzat took on the role of CEO at Capgemini. I now still remain Chairman of the Board.

I joined the Capgemini Group in 1993, after fifteen years working in the French government, primarily in the ministry of Finance, where I held a number of posts in the Budget Office and on various ministry staffs, including that of Finance Minister Jacques Delors. Before joining Capgemini Group, I was chief of staff to Dominique Strauss-Kahn, Minister of Industry and Trade, from 1991 to 1993.

Initially overseeing central functions at Capgemini Group, I became CEO of Cap Gemini France in 1996, taking a seat on Cap Gemini’s Directoire in May 1996. I was then named deputy CEO of the Group and Board member in May 2000 after initiating the merger of Capgemini and Ernst & Young Consulting. I was appointed CEO of the Capgemini Group in 2002, after the Board of Directors accepted Serge Kampf’s proposal, and then also took on the additional role of Chairman of the Capgemini Group in May 2012. 

Outside of Capgemini, as part of the emphasis on economic diplomacy, Laurent Fabius, French Minister of Foreign Affairs, appointed me in January 2013 as Special Representative for the economic relationship with India.

I am also Chairman of THE BRIDGE SAS, incubator of startups and corporate open innovation based at Avignon (France) promoting French Tech Culture Avignon Provence. And I was appointed Chairman of the Opera Festival of Aix-en-Provence in June 2018. 

I graduated from the Ecole Polytechnique in 1972 and the Ecole Nationale d’Administration (ENA) in 1978.

description:
Ekta Kapoor is the Joint Managing Director and Creative Director of the much-acclaimed Balaji Telefilms Ltd., Balaji Motion Pictures and Alt Balaji. She is the force behind revamping India’s television landscape with her iconic content like Kyunki Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi, Kahaani Ghar Ghar Ki, Kasauti Zindagi Ki and Naagin etc.

She started her career at the age of 18 with scripting and TV production and created Balaji Telefilms. While Television became her forte, she challenged herself more and she ventured into the big screen with a genre that was very different from the serials and created Balaji Motion pictures in the year 2001. With a vision of creating orbit-breaking content that caters to all demography, Balaji Motion Pictures has given films like Dirty Picture, Udta Punjab and Lipstick Under My Burkha.
 
With the changing times in Digital and International competition by Netflix & Amazon, she forayed into digital world and as a result created ALT Digital Media Entertainment Limited (ALT Balaji) in 2015, a homegrown app with a vision to reach out directly to individual audiences, by providing them with original, exclusive and tailor-made shows that they can access at their fingertips.
She has been accredited for creating the infamous Kyunki Saas Bhi Kabhi Bahu Thi, the only show on Indian television serial to achieve a TRP of 22.4. With the changing times, shows like Pyaar Kii Ye Ek Kahaani, Gumrah: End of Innocence, MTV Webbed that resonates with the youth were also produced
. 
A production house started in 1994 by Ekta Kapoor, Balaji Telefilms ltd. marks a legacy of 24 years. The vision has been to consistently provide delightful and innovative entertainment experiences by engaging audiences and nurturing talent. In the legacy of 24 years, Ekta Kapoor has produced more than 188+ shows in Hindi, Marathi, Kannada, Tamil, Malayalam, Bengali, Bhojpuri and Punjabi.

description:
Solomon Choi is a seasoned F&B entrepreneur, investor, and advisor with over 20 years of experience in the hospitality industry. He is the CEO of Jabba Brands, a company he founded in 2019 to advise, invest, and operate companies that improve the way people eat, drink, and live harmoniously. He is also an Angel Squad Member at Hustle Fund, a venture capital firm that invests in early-stage startups in various sectors, including F&B.

Before Jabba Brands, Solomon founded and sold two successful F&B companies: 16 Handles, New York City's first self-serve frozen yogurt shop that grew to over 40 locations internationally, and Greeno Products, a supplier of custom and off-the-shelf disposables for the food service industry. Both companies were bootstrapped for almost 15 years each, without outside investment, and generated 8-figure and 7-figure revenues respectively. Solomon has also invested in and advised multiple F&B-related companies and startups, such as Lunchbox, Sanzo, and Kolkata Chai Co., helping them scale to become best-in-class brands.

Solomon's core competencies include franchising, go-to-market strategy, restaurant technology, and bootstrapped growth. He holds a BS in Business Administration from USC Marshall School of Business and certifications in Restaurant Revenue Management and Digital Marketing from eCornell. He speaks English, Korean, and has a Beginner's Mandarin certification from Tsinghua University. Solomon enjoys speaking to students, entrepreneurs, and organizations, and sharing his insights and expertise on F&B and entrepreneurship. His mission is to build leading F&B brands that people love and positively impact the world.

- In 2023, Vay became the first and is still today the only company to be fully driverless on public streets in Europe (Hamburg) 
- In May 2023, Thomas von der Ohe, the CEO and Co-Founder of Vay was awarded as founder of the year 2023 from the German start-up federation. Previous year winner: Jochen Engert from Flixbus. Keynote speech: Chancellor Olaf Scholz

About Vay:
- Vay pursues a different approach towards driverless mobility: remote driving (aka "teledriving")
- We want to bring forward green, sustainable transportation to achieve a positive impact on societies across the globe. From Europe.
- Our first application: 1. You click a button in the VayApp; 2. A teledriver brings you an electric car within a few minutes; 3. You drive it to your final destination and leave the car; 4. No need to park it as another teledriver takes care of that
- We aim to introduce autonomous functions in our system gradually and based on high-quality teledrive data
- Vay’s 150+ team members have previously worked at companies such as Tesla, Google, Waymo, Zoox, Amazon, Uber as well as Audi, BMW, and Daimler. 
- Funded with $100+M to date, Vay became the highest funded European startup in the self-driving car industry with its Series B
- For more information: www.vay.io


Before Vay:
Together with great teams, I've shipped our own dynamic carpool solution, the 1st Amazon Echo, the 1st Amazon Tap and the 1st public road testing for a self driving car at Zoox in the Silicon Valley. 
I hold a M.Sc. in MS&E with focus on Computer Science & Entrepreneurship from Stanford University.

I'd also love to help push technology & entrepreneurship in Europe! So if you think I can help in any way, please reach out.

description:
I previously served as the Head of Global Cyber Security for Ubisoft, where I led all efforts in information security. My group protected over 20,000 employees worldwide with a vast scope (see job desc for more)

In my previous roles such as Director of Penetration Testing, I led efforts on matters of information security consulting. The gamut stretched from developing penetration testing plans for Fortune 100 companies to competing in "bake-offs" to win business against other top-tier consulting vendors. 

I have also served as a Director of Operations, leading teams of highly technical Application Security Engineers and Technical Operations staff. In this role, I was an extension of (and advisor to) over 300+ security programs across many industry verticals. Under my direction, my team triaged over 22,000 vulnerabilities in 2018-2019 alone. 

Personally, I love being in the trenches and performing actual assessments, but I am also adept at handling clients, architecting solutions, designing services, improving business processes, managing technical consultants, training, technical writing, marketing, and delivering solutions. 

While my strengths are web, network/infrastructural, and mobile security, I have personally performed a myriad of other services and implemented them for a consultancy as a deliverable (mainframe, wireless, cloud assessment, database, OSINT, APT simulation, binary reversing, and static code analysis).

In my free time, I write for several information security publications and am a semi-regular capture-the-flag player. I speak regularly at security conferences globally (DEFCON, Blackhat, OWASP, and many more)

While I never call myself a "master" of anything, I do have a very particular set of skills; skills I have acquired over a very long career. These skills make me adept at helping businesses, finding security vulnerabilities, and leading a business to a better security posture.
headline: CEO | Hacker | Trainer at Arcanum Information Security

description:
Hi, I'm Daniel - co-founder of Lilium. ✈️

The all-electric Lilium Jet combines the flexibility of a VTOL aircraft with the efficiency of a traditional fixed-wing aircraft, resulting in industry-leading maximum range and speed. 

Thanks to our ducted fan technology, flying with a Lilium Jet will be fast, comfortable, CO2-emissons free and quiet.   

What started as an idea by 4 students at the Technical University of Munich in 2015 has grown into a NASDAQ-listed, EASA DOA-certified company with over 1000 employees, including more than 500 aerospace engineers and a leadership team responsible for delivering some of the most successful aircraft in aviation history.    

During my time as CEO, I had the opportunity to lead the company to several key milestones, including the first flight of our technology demonstrator in 2019, multiple rounds of fundraising leading up to the company's IPO in 2021, and building a strong, dedicated team of industry leaders.  

In 2022, I handed over the CEO role to Klaus Roewe, who brings with him more than 30 years of experience at Airbus, where he was responsible for the A320neo development, the A320 program and global Customer Service.
   
In my role as Chief Engineer for Innovation and Future Programs, I am now focusing on the development of battery technology, future technologies and the vision of the company.

description:
Andrea Orcel is Group Chief Executive Officer of UniCredit, where he is leading the pan-European bank through a process of digitalisation and simplification, underpinned by an unwavering focus on its clients. 

He is one of Europe’s leading banking experts, with a proven track record of success in senior roles at several major financial institutions around the world. During his career as a senior investment banker, Andrea Orcel has orchestrated several of the most innovative and complex mergers & acquisitions and capital market transactions globally.

After beginning his career at Midland Montagu, Goldman Sachs and Boston Consulting Group, Andrea Orcel spent seventeen years at Merrill Lynch where he progressed through various roles serving the bank’s global market to become Head of Global Origination. Following this, he spent three years at the Bank of America culminating in his role as Executive Chairman of the Investment Bank and President of Emerging Markets. 

In 2012, Andrea Orcel joined UBS where he served as President of the Investment Bank, CEO of UBS UK and Member of the UBS Group Executive Board. During his six-year tenure at the bank, Andrea Orcel managed diverse businesses across multiple geographies, designed and executed the UBS Investment Bank turnaround transforming it into one of the leading businesses renowned for its efficiency, integrity and winning culture, and established a capital-light, higher-risk growth model which now serves as a blueprint for the industry. 

In addition to his corporate career Andrea Orcel has served as Member of the Board of UBS Optimus Foundation, Senior Sponsor and Leader for Diversity and Talent Development for UBS Investment Bank and UBS UK. 

Andrea Orcel graduated with a BA in Economics and Commerce from the University of Rome in 1986 and received his MBA from INSEAD in 1990. He lives with his wife and daughter.
headline: Group Chief Executive Officer of UniCredit

description:
As Executive Chairman of Wipro, an $11.2 billion global information technology, consulting, and business process services company, Rishad provides direction and strategic insight to the business and Wipro’s leadership team.

Rishad believes that culture is a firm's strongest asset, and works tirelessly to ensure every Wipro-ite understands and upholds the values of Wipro, articulated as the Spirit of Wipro.

Rishad joined Wipro in 2007 and worked in several roles before becoming Executive Chairman in 2019. 
Until recently, he was the Chief Strategy Officer, responsible for shaping Wipro's strategy and growth. He conceptualised Wipro Ventures – Wipro's strategic investment arm that invests in start-ups that are developing next-generation products and technologies. 

Rishad is on the Board of Wipro Enterprises, and the Wipro-GE joint venture. He is also on the Board of Azim Premji Foundation - one of the largest not-for-profit initiatives in India - that works with over 350,000 government schools across seven states in India to improve the state of primary education.  Separately, he is also on the Board of Azim Premji Philanthropic Initiatives.

Rishad was the Chairman of NASSCOM, the trade body of India’s $170 billion software industry, in 2018-2019.

Prior to joining Wipro Limited in 2007, Rishad has worked with Bain & Company in London, and GE Capital in the US. In 2014, he was recognised as a Young Global Leader by the World Economic Forum, for his leadership, professional accomplishments, and commitment to society.
headline: Executive Chairman, Wipro Limited

description:
Ron is the CEO and Co-Founder of Enjoy, the first mobile retail store. Enjoy has partnered with premier technology companies including AT&T, Rogers, and British Telecom to bring their products directly to customers. When a partner's customer purchases on-line, their product is hand delivered on-demand, with a trained Expert to get them up and running, answer any questions, and purchase any additional products, accessories, or software solutions. Under Ron's leadership, Enjoy has delivered more than one million Enjoy experiences and created a new channel in retail - the mobile store. 

Ron is perhaps best known for the work he did creating and leading the Apple Stores during their first twelve years. Ron also served as the CEO of JCPenney during 2012 and 2013. Prior to his time at Apple Ron was highly regarded for the work he did as the merchant leader at Target Stores, the United States leading upscale Discount Stores. He helped the 1700 store Target chain differentiate itself through design and skillful marketing. Ron spent the majority of his 15 years at Target from 1984 through 2000 in merchandising leadership positions. 

In addition, Ron is a Board Member of several private companies in the Bay Area.
headline: Chief Executive Officer at Enjoy Inc.
